Investec, which provides asset management and specialist banking services, has been streamlining its operations by selling and shutting some units and restructuring businesses. Investec's London-listed shares fell as much as 10% in early deals to lead fallers in the mid-cap index .FTMC, after it revealed costs would nearly double to 42 million pounds ($53 million) and headline earnings per share are expected to be 15% to 18% down on At 1010 GMT, the stock was trading down 6.1%

In a pre-close trading update, Investec said the hike in costs related to the closure of its private equity direct investments business in Hong Kong, part of its UK wealth operation and the restructuring of its Irish branch in preparation for Britainâ€™s exit from the European Union, although this was partially offset by the sale of its Irish wealth management business.
